  "body": "### Description\n\nThe current version of `QuarkusAsyncHealthCheckFactory` calls `MutinyHelper.blockingExecutor(vertx)` which defaults to an ordered execution of the health checks. This prevents them to be executed in parallel. \r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/86c7988ea28b5b78c8706a50da41dd1d95cb4b74/extensions/smallrye-health/runtime/src/main/java/io/quarkus/smallrye/health/runtime/QuarkusAsyncHealthCheckFactory.java#L31-L35\r\n\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nInstead, it should call `MutinyHelper.blockingExecutor(vertx, false)`. \r\n\r\nI'll prepare a pull request.",
